sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Training Operator Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS (self-signed)
    participant Controller as Training Operator Controller<br/>controller-runtime
    participant DNS as Kubernetes DNS<br/>53/UDP
    participant Master as Master Pod<br/>(via headless service)
    participant Workers as Worker Pods<br/>(via headless service)

    Note over User,Workers: Flow 1: Distributed PyTorch Training Job Lifecycle

    User->>K8sAPI: 1. kubectl create PyTorchJob<br/>HTTPS/443, Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: 2. Admission review<br/>HTTPS/9443, API server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validated (or rejected)
    K8sAPI-->>User: PyTorchJob created

    K8sAPI->>Controller: 3. Watch event (PyTorchJob)<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 4. Create headless Service<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 4. Create Master Pod<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 4. Create Worker Pods<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token

    Workers->>DNS: 5. Resolve master hostname<br/>DNS/53 UDP
    DNS-->>Workers: Master Pod IP

    Workers->>Master: 6. Connect for distributed training<br/>TCP (per job config, no encryption)
    Master-->>Workers: Training coordination (gradients, parameters)

    Note over Controller,Workers: Controller monitors pod status, handles restarts, updates job status

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update PyTorchJob status<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token

    Note over User,Workers: Flow 2: MPI Job Communication Pattern

    participant Launcher as MPI Launcher Pod<br/>(with kubectl-delivery init)
    participant MPIWorkers as MPI Worker Pods

    Controller->>K8sAPI: 1. Create ConfigMap (hostfile, scripts)<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 1. Create ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 1. Create Launcher + Worker Pods<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token

    Note over Launcher: 2. Init container copies kubectl<br/>binary from kubectl-delivery image

    Launcher->>K8sAPI: 3. kubectl exec into workers<br/>HTTPS/443, per-job SA Token
    K8sAPI->>MPIWorkers: 4. Execute MPI commands<br/>Kubernetes exec, TLS 1.2+<br/>RBAC: pods/exec on specific pod names

    MPIWorkers-->>Launcher: MPI results
